00:28:01,315 --> 00:28:06,012
and then boom, suddenly, "hello, hi, you're a witch,
and by the way so is your whole family",

507
00:28:06,303 --> 00:28:10,807
and we're saving innocents, and then I'm somebody's wife,
and then I'm somebody's mother, and then I'm somebody's boss,

508
00:28:10,807 --> 00:28:12,115
and I'm somebody something.

509
00:28:13,620 --> 00:28:15,817
And I just...

510
00:28:16,046 --> 00:28:17,599
I don't know how to start over.

511
00:28:17,599 --> 00:28:20,579
I've been wo many things for so long.

512
00:28:21,357 --> 00:28:23,236
I don't know who I am anymore.

513
00:28:24,287 --> 00:28:25,806
I know who you are.

514
00:28:27,898 --> 00:28:29,555
You're an amazing mum.

515
00:28:30,987 --> 00:28:32,628
And you're an amazing wife.

516
00:28:33,684 --> 00:28:35,548
And most importantly, an amazing person.

517
00:28:36,045 --> 00:28:36,873
Stop.

518
00:28:37,287 --> 00:28:38,719
No, you are.

519
00:28:38,737 --> 00:28:43,923
You can't sacrify yourself for so many people
for so many years

520
00:28:44,313 --> 00:28:45,990
and not expect a transition period.

521
00:28:47,288 --> 00:28:48,466
You have to be patient.

522
00:28:49,252 --> 00:28:50,634
And what do I do about the guilt?

523
00:28:50,947 --> 00:28:51,980
What guilt?

524
00:28:51,980 --> 00:28:55,158
The guilt I feel when I know very bad things are happening out there

525
00:28:55,158 --> 00:28:57,370
and I'm not doing anything about it.

526
00:28:57,511 --> 00:28:59,327
Like these missing kids.

527
00:28:59,971 --> 00:29:02,058
Bad things are always gonna happen, Piper.

528
00:29:03,057 --> 00:29:05,114
You know, they happened long before you became a witch,

529
00:29:05,114 --> 00:29:07,772
and they're gonna continue to happen long afterwards.

530
00:29:09,563 --> 00:29:10,753
You've paid your dues.

531
00:29:10,753 --> 00:29:13,734
You've been selfless, now it's time to be selfish.

532
00:29:15,076 --> 00:29:16,160
You deserve it.

533
00:29:17,452 --> 00:29:19,233
We all do.

534
00:29:35,325 --> 00:29:39,611
- We've got to stop meeting like this.
- Yeah, how you say?

535
00:29:39,994 --> 00:29:42,909
<i>Sometimes signs are settled, easily missed.</i>

536
00:29:42,910 --> 00:29:47,465
<i>But if you're lucky enough to catch them,
they tend to send you in the right direction.</i>

537
00:29:49,963 --> 00:29:51,614
<i>On the other hand, if you miss them,</i>

538
00:29:51,948 --> 00:29:53,357
<i>they can bite you in the ass.</i>

539
00:29:53,884 --> 00:29:54,675
<i>Big time.</i>

540
00:29:55,100 --> 00:29:56,532
You dropped something?

541
00:30:05,108 --> 00:30:06,703
Nice costum. Where did you get it?

542
00:30:06,703 --> 00:30:07,904
Sax, you like it?

543
00:30:07,904 --> 00:30:10,033
No, witches don't actually wear costums.

544
00:30:10,033 --> 00:30:13,187
Oh really?
So they cannot go out in a broomstick that she's everyday wearing?

545
00:30:13,187 --> 00:30:14,266
I meant recently.

546
00:30:14,266 --> 00:30:15,580
You should be more specific.

547
00:30:15,838 --> 00:30:17,889
I'll try to remember that for next time. Thanks for the tip.

548
00:30:19,004 --> 00:30:20,114
What's your name anyway?

549
00:30:20,608 --> 00:30:21,250
What's yours?

550
00:30:22,611 --> 00:30:23,085
Jo.

551
00:30:25,871 --> 00:30:26,669
Billie.

552
00:30:27,043 --> 00:30:27,483
Well, Billie,

553
00:30:27,980 --> 00:30:31,230
it seems as if we have a big problem here.

554
00:30:31,230 --> 00:30:35,075
Oh yeah?
You know actually, my problem is

555
00:30:35,085 --> 00:30:37,198
that you're just killing my buzz.

556
00:30:39,033 --> 00:30:42,195
"Buzz", that's what you're calling fighting demons?

557
00:30:42,195 --> 00:30:43,988
Beats the hell out of video games!

558
00:30:44,147 --> 00:30:45,680
This isn't a game, ok?

559
00:30:46,227 --> 00:30:47,870
This is real, deadly real.

560
00:30:47,870 --> 00:30:49,992
You can't use an adverb with a noun.

561
00:30:50,445 --> 00:30:51,991
Chair!

562
00:30:57,982 --> 00:30:59,476
Ok, here is the thing.

563
00:30:59,794 --> 00:31:01,098
People are getting killed.

564
00:31:01,098 --> 00:31:04,469
So you are gonna tell me everything I want to know

565
00:31:04,554 --> 00:31:07,449
and you're gonna tell it to me now,
otherwise we're gonna go out again.

566
00:31:08,182 --> 00:31:09,047
Fine, I'm listenning.

567
00:31:09,277 --> 00:31:10,536
How long have you been a witch?

568
00:31:10,536 --> 00:31:16,417
Not that long, just up to really recently,
I noticed I had these... these powers.

569
00:31:16,920 --> 00:31:19,006
So I bought a couple of books and I figured it out.

570
00:31:19,352 --> 00:31:20,964
And you figured out how to track demons that way?

571
00:31:21,273 --> 00:31:22,038
I'm good.

572
00:31:22,541 --> 00:31:23,396
Well, I am.

573
00:31:24,219 --> 00:31:25,191
Look, let me...

574
00:31:25,931 --> 00:31:26,787
May I?

575
00:31:29,503 --> 00:31:30,979
Ok, well, first,

576
00:31:31,640 --> 00:31:34,956
I noticed that all the missing kids had Alice like names.

577
00:31:35,440 --> 00:31:39,505
You know like Alicia, Alyson, Allister, Alex.

578
00:31:39,758 --> 00:31:40,855
This has to do with what?

579
00:31:40,855 --> 00:31:41,747
Alice?

580
00:31:41,747 --> 00:31:43,348
You know, like Alice in Wonderland?

581
00:31:45,019 --> 00:31:47,724
Ok, when the victims were found,
they were saying all these weird things,

582
00:31:48,063 --> 00:31:51,236
like mad hatters, white rabbits, stone caterpillars.

583
00:31:51,237 --> 00:31:53,577
It had to be something demonic, right?
It wasn't just too cool not to be.

584
00:31:54,152 --> 00:31:57,766
No, actually demonic isn't so cool. It's kind of a bad thing.

585
00:31:57,767 --> 00:32:01,009
Ok, whatever.
Anyways. I input it all in the computer,

586
00:32:02,134 --> 00:32:03,922
I hoped the crystal act like a GPS system,

587
00:32:03,922 --> 00:32:06,846
I started scrying for the demon, and voilà, there he was.

588
00:32:07,457 --> 00:32:10,222
Or there she was. Are most demons chicks?

589
00:32:10,896 --> 00:32:12,515
No, no, not always.

590
00:32:13,003 --> 00:32:15,925
You figured this all out by yourself?

591
00:32:16,295 --> 00:32:19,966
- Yeah.
- Ok, in that case I'm gonna need you to stay put while I go dealing with this.

592
00:32:19,966 --> 00:32:21,202
Wait, what?

593
00:32:21,713 --> 00:32:23,671
You're in way over your head, Billie.
That's why yo called for my help.

594
00:32:24,009 --> 00:32:25,398
I did not called for you.

595
00:32:26,376 --> 00:32:28,714
Just let me and my sisters deal with this, ok?

596
00:32:28,714 --> 00:32:31,825
Wait, what, sisters? Are they witches too?

597
00:32:33,508 --> 00:32:35,725
Just stay here. I'll be back.

598
00:32:37,014 --> 00:32:38,208
Stay!

599
00:32:52,936 --> 00:32:54,006
Hey Julie.

600
00:32:55,172 --> 00:32:57,708
Dex, hey.
What are you doing here?

601
00:32:58,312 --> 00:33:01,246
Well you know I just stop by and see how things went with the tribune.

602
00:33:02,244 --> 00:33:04,886
- Actually it has nothing to do with the tribune.
- No?

603
00:33:05,519 --> 00:33:09,341
No. Apparently the newspaper is having a hard time getting the advice column out

604
00:33:10,768 --> 00:33:12,681
- ever since, you know.
- Yeah.

605
00:33:13,071 --> 00:33:14,777
So they asked me to help out a little bit,

606
00:33:15,071 --> 00:33:19,332
which I thought was kind of weird, but I said sure.
Because I'm here and I'm not doing anything.

607
00:33:20,139 --> 00:33:21,924
You look like you're enjoying yourself.

608
00:33:23,618 --> 00:33:29,351
Oh, hey, get this to copy right away
and make sure that "weird and warmer creek" is before "abandonned Boston"

609
00:33:29,654 --> 00:33:31,835
because it just flows better, ok? Thanks.

610
00:33:34,904 --> 00:33:35,597
Dead lines.

611
00:33:35,597 --> 00:33:38,152
I wonder what made them ask you of all people?

612
00:33:38,728 --> 00:33:39,663
I don't know.

613
00:33:40,211 --> 00:33:42,543
They said something about who being...

614
00:33:42,543 --> 00:33:44,235
Might run in the family?

615
00:33:45,492 --> 00:33:47,990
Yes, that's exactly what they said.

616
00:33:49,911 --> 00:33:52,193
Wait a minute. Did you have...

617
00:33:52,193 --> 00:33:55,000
I ran into here after the elevator, I told her I thought,

618
00:33:55,468 --> 00:33:56,900
you might be able to help.

619
00:33:58,456 --> 00:34:00,342
Anything better than the crap they've been printing, right?

620
00:34:01,291 --> 00:34:03,660
Yeah. Thanks, I think.

621
00:34:04,756 --> 00:34:06,858
Look, I was just trying to protect your cousin's column.

622
00:34:07,671 --> 00:34:08,629
I was her biggest fan.

623
00:34:09,997 --> 00:34:10,773
I can see that.

624
00:34:12,615 --> 00:34:14,617
It's too bad you've never got to know her.

625
00:34:16,285 --> 00:34:20,442
Well, maybe you can catch me above at diner?

626
00:34:22,136 --> 00:34:25,619
<i>A fourth victim, Alex Robbins,18, had just been discovered,</i>

627
00:34:25,874 --> 00:34:28,990
<i>walking down in the middle of Market Street, without any sense of who she was</i>

628
00:34:29,336 --> 00:34:30,574
<i>or what she was doing.</i>

629
00:34:30,941 --> 00:34:34,521
<i>Witnesses say that like the others she was found mumbling incoherently.</i>

630
00:34:34,868 --> 00:34:38,494
<i>In this case, about a path that leads no where and smiles without faces.</i>

631
00:34:38,787 --> 00:34:39,872
"Smiles without faces..."

632
00:34:40,609 --> 00:34:42,213
What the hell is going on out there.

633
00:34:43,451 --> 00:34:44,780
I have to go now.

634
00:34:44,780 --> 00:34:47,646
- What?
- I'll call you. I'm sorry.

635
00:34:53,109 --> 00:34:55,059
The teens are being lured by a fairy tale.

636
00:34:55,492 --> 00:34:57,510
Yeah, Alice in Wonderland. We know.

637
00:34:57,510 --> 00:34:58,815
What do you mean you know?

638
00:34:59,139 --> 00:35:00,510
- Billie.
- Billie?

639
00:35:00,510 --> 00:35:01,404
Who is Billie?

640
00:35:01,404 --> 00:35:02,581
Paige's new charge.

641
00:35:02,581 --> 00:35:05,832
What I don't understand is why Alice in Wonderland?
Why did the demon pick that one?

642
00:35:05,832 --> 00:35:08,868
Are you kidding?
It's all about the loss of innocence,

643
00:35:09,272 --> 00:35:12,447
the need for escape,
the search for one's identity.

644
00:35:12,964 --> 00:35:15,856
Well if that's the case, I'm surprised they didn't lure us too.

645
00:35:15,856 --> 00:35:17,054
Maybe it was meant to.

646
00:35:17,501 --> 00:35:19,601
What else a demon would go through all that trouble,

647
00:35:19,940 --> 00:35:21,615
what, just to mess up a couple of kids?

648
00:35:21,977 --> 00:35:22,552
Possibly.

649
00:35:22,898 --> 00:35:25,148
I think these signs are too elaborate not to be meant for us.

650
00:35:25,148 --> 00:35:26,005
And Billie.

651
00:35:26,408 --> 00:35:28,163
No, I don't think it was meant for her.

652
00:35:28,438 --> 00:35:29,288
I think she just found it.

653
00:35:29,288 --> 00:35:31,143
Which makes her one smart witch.

654
00:35:31,410 --> 00:35:33,586
Yeah, maybe too smart for our own good I think.

655
00:35:33,586 --> 00:35:35,073
Do you think it is a trap?

656
00:35:35,302 --> 00:35:36,230
It could be.

657
00:35:36,663 --> 00:35:39,368
Ok, then what do we do?
I mean we can't go after the demon.

658
00:35:39,745 --> 00:35:42,121
If we don't do anything, more innocents will be hurt.

659
00:35:42,475 --> 00:35:43,766
Innocents are always gonna get hurt.

660
00:35:43,766 --> 00:35:47,172
I know Leo, but it's a little bit different,
when we're aware of it.

661
00:35:47,626 --> 00:35:49,548
I don't think this is something we can ignore.

662
00:35:51,878 --> 00:35:53,024
So how do we find them?

663
00:35:53,266 --> 00:35:54,159
Billie knows how.

664
00:35:54,254 --> 00:35:56,844
I'll go get her scrying stuff
and you stay and make a potion, ok?

665
00:35:57,079 --> 00:35:58,338
What if she figures this out?

666
00:35:58,670 --> 00:36:02,134
I don't think she's gonna figure this out
because to her, it is all just a lovely little game.

667
00:36:02,134 --> 00:36:04,997
Yeah well it's one we'd better win.

668
00:36:17,000 --> 00:36:18,331
We've been waiting for you.

669
00:36:24,957 --> 00:36:26,130
Oh, I'm curious.

670
00:36:26,649 --> 00:36:27,655
Which one are you?

671
00:36:27,812 --> 00:36:28,407
Phoebe?

672
00:36:28,982 --> 00:36:29,616
Piper?

673
00:36:30,035 --> 00:36:30,841
Paige?

674
00:36:30,876 --> 00:36:33,408
I think you have me confuse with somebody else.

675
00:36:33,688 --> 00:36:35,134
I think not.

676
00:36:36,616 --> 00:36:37,414
Send her through.

677
00:36:37,861 --> 00:36:41,625
Then after the sisters find her lying in the street and
come looking for revenge,

678
00:36:42,169 --> 00:36:44,574
we will send them through too.

679
00:36:51,443 --> 00:36:52,064
Where is Billie?

680
00:36:52,730 --> 00:36:56,362
In big trouble.
She decided to go after the demon by herself.

681
00:36:56,640 --> 00:36:58,230
- What?
- A way to find her?

682
00:36:59,353 --> 00:37:00,171
I think so.

683
00:37:00,445 --> 00:37:03,694
I took this from her computer showing me how she scryied.

684
00:37:03,694 --> 00:37:05,814
She was scrying with a computer?

685
00:37:05,814 --> 00:37:07,267
Pretty style there.

686
00:37:07,743 --> 00:37:10,313
Right. Or it just might get her killed faster.

687
00:37:12,322 --> 00:37:12,854
I got her.

688
00:37:14,098 --> 00:37:15,767
Hang on a second, wait one second.

689
00:37:16,285 --> 00:37:18,300
What if Billie doesn't need saving.

690
00:37:18,764 --> 00:37:19,431
What?

691
00:37:19,431 --> 00:37:21,317
Do you have any idea what she's talking about?

692
00:37:21,317 --> 00:37:24,735
I'm talking about what if Billie is part of the trap.

693
00:37:25,132 --> 00:37:26,347
That is absurd.

694
00:37:26,787 --> 00:37:27,441
Is it?

695
00:37:27,859 --> 00:37:30,299
Think about it.
Either she's as smart as you think she is,

696
00:37:30,616 --> 00:37:33,163
and she figured all of it out by herself, or

697
00:37:33,487 --> 00:37:34,754
she's working with the demons.

698
00:37:35,113 --> 00:37:35,934
Oh please.

699
00:37:36,444 --> 00:37:38,439
Come on Paige, how well do you really know her?

700
00:37:38,935 --> 00:37:41,324
She could have planted all of the signs.

701
00:38:09,608 --> 00:38:10,550
Help!

702
00:38:10,662 --> 00:38:12,100
Kill her! I said kill her!

703
00:38:12,371 --> 00:38:15,827
Cut her, right now, on with her head!

704
00:38:17,075 --> 00:38:18,249
Run for your life!

705
00:38:24,972 --> 00:38:26,987
What is happenning to me?

706
00:38:28,138 --> 00:38:30,095
"I'll be the judge and the jury."

707
00:38:30,317 --> 00:38:31,967
said the cunning old Fury...

708
00:38:32,085 --> 00:38:35,447
And I'll trial the whole case,
then condemn you to death.

709
00:38:47,260 --> 00:38:49,297
- Billie are you in there?
- Yeah.

710
00:38:54,030 --> 00:38:54,930
What have you done?

711
00:38:55,513 --> 00:38:56,593
How did you do this?

712
00:38:57,211 --> 00:38:58,225
You killed her.

713
00:38:58,802 --> 00:39:01,436
Brightside, at least you got to meet us first.

714
00:39:01,436 --> 00:39:03,372
I should never have underestimated you.

715
00:39:04,156 --> 00:39:05,509
I knew you're alive.

716
00:39:05,509 --> 00:39:08,545
Too bad, you won't be around long enough to tell anybody.

717
00:39:20,827 --> 00:39:21,247
Waouh!

718
00:39:21,569 --> 00:39:22,423
You're welcome.

719
00:39:22,792 --> 00:39:25,687
I can't believe this.
You guys really are the Charmed Ones?

720
00:39:27,937 --> 00:39:30,053
I did a little research after you left.

721
00:39:30,467 --> 00:39:32,978
The newspapers said you all died in a terrible accident.

722
00:39:34,496 --> 00:39:35,458
And which one are you?

723
00:39:40,116 --> 00:39:41,454
I would be Paige.

724
00:39:41,577 --> 00:39:42,778
What do we do?

725
00:39:42,778 --> 00:39:44,257
Blow her up.

726
00:39:44,387 --> 00:39:46,387
What? Do you have any better ideas?

727
00:39:46,672 --> 00:39:48,738
I'm not gonna tell anyone if that what you think. I promise.

728
00:39:49,029 --> 00:39:49,779
What's the catch?

729
00:39:51,374 --> 00:39:52,045
Well, show me the ropes,

730
00:39:52,527 --> 00:39:54,749
teach me everything you know about witchcraft.

731
00:39:55,002 --> 00:39:55,495
Everything.

732
00:39:55,999 --> 00:39:57,761
- Forget it.
- Wait a second.

733
00:39:59,015 --> 00:39:59,962
What do you have to offer?

734
00:40:00,947 --> 00:40:03,690
I can help you guys fight the demons.
You don't have to do it all the time.

735
00:40:03,914 --> 00:40:06,534
I mean, I assume that is why you faked your own deaths, right?

736
00:40:07,614 --> 00:40:09,870
You're right. She is too smart for our own good.

737
00:40:10,727 --> 00:40:11,153
Alright.

738
00:40:11,494 --> 00:40:12,518
One condition.

739
00:40:13,822 --> 00:40:15,485
Lose the cheap leather outfit.

740
00:40:19,303 --> 00:40:20,064
Sorry.

741
00:40:24,414 --> 00:40:26,721
<i>It's funny sometimes where signs lead you.</i>

742
00:40:29,290 --> 00:40:30,779
<i>Rarely where you thought you'd go,</i>

743
00:40:31,926 --> 00:40:33,914
<i>but always where you belong.</i>

744
00:40:37,413 --> 00:40:41,505
<i>In Paige's case, she realized that being a cop wasn't her cup of tea,</i>

745
00:40:42,171 --> 00:40:44,125
<i>being with a certain cop was.</i>

746
00:40:46,123 --> 00:40:50,938
<i>For Piper, the only sign she really needed was the one that reminded her she wasn't alone.</i>

747
00:41:06,010 --> 00:41:09,466
<i>As for me, I discovered that, just like Alice,</i>

748
00:41:09,466 --> 00:41:11,123
<i>no matter how wild the ride,</i>

749
00:41:11,123 --> 00:41:15,315
<i>signs will sometimes lead you right back to where you started from.</i>

750
00:41:16,536 --> 00:41:17,214
<i>Changed,</i>

751
00:41:18,014 --> 00:41:18,624
<i>different,</i>

752
00:41:19,290 --> 00:41:21,031
<i>but home.</i>

753
00:41:38,088 --> 00:41:42,270
<i>And they lived happily ever after....</i>

